events.name: Oregon Ducks at California Golden Bears

headlines.description: Jeff Maehl caught a 29-yard pass for the only touchdown by No. 1 Oregon's usually high-powered offense, but the Ducks' defense shut down California in a 15-13 victory over the Golden Bears on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Oregon needs D to thwart pesky Cal

events.name: Georgia Bulldogs at Auburn Tigers

headlines.description: Cam Newton responded to allegations of wrongdoing with another brilliant performance Saturday, passing for two touchdowns and running for two more to lead No. 2 Auburn into the Southeastern Conference championship game with a 49-31 victory over Georgia.

events.name: San Diego State Aztecs at TCU Horned Frogs

headlines.description: Andy Dalton threw three touchdown passes to Jeremy Kerley as third-ranked TCU rallied from an early two-touchdown deficit, then held on for a 40-35 victory over San Diego State on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 3 TCU holds off SDSU's late push

events.name: Louisiana Monroe Warhawks at LSU Tigers

headlines.description: Ron Brooks returned an interception for a score, Lavar Edwards brought back a fumble for another, and LSU's defense dominated throughout the fifth-ranked Tigers' 51-0 blowout of Louisiana-Monroe on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LSU's opportunistic defense paves way for romp

events.name: Stanford Cardinal at Arizona State Sun Devils

headlines.description: Andrew Luck threw for 292 yards and engineered a long fourth-quarter scoring drive to set up Owen Marecic's second 1-yard touchdown dive, lifting No. 7 Stanford to a defensive-dominated 17-13 win over Arizona State Saturday night.

events.name: Indiana Hoosiers at Wisconsin Badgers

headlines.description: Montee Ball ran for three touchdowns in his first career start, replacing injured running back John Clay, and Scott Tolzien threw for three more as Wisconsin routed Indiana 83-20 on Saturday.

events.name: Kansas Jayhawks at Nebraska Cornhuskers

headlines.description: — There have been plenty of years that Kansas has struggled to beat teams from the Football Championship Subdivision to open the season, and second-year coach Lance Leipold is keenly aware of that fact.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jayhawks pound away in 56-10 victory over Tennessee Tech

events.name: Penn State Nittany Lions at Ohio State Buckeyes

headlines.description: Devon Torrence tipped and snagged an interception and returned it 34 yards for the go-ahead touchdown to turn the tide in Ohio State's 38-14 win over Penn State on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Torrence turns tide as Ohio St. tips Penn St.

events.name: Oklahoma State Cowboys at Texas Longhorns

headlines.description: Brandon Weeden passed for 409 yards and Kendall Hunter had two rushing touchdowns as No. 12 Oklahoma State ended a 12-year losing streak to Texas with a 33-16 victory Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Okla. St. ends 12-year slide vs. Texas

events.name: Mississippi State Bulldogs at Alabama Crimson Tide

headlines.description: Greg McElroy passed for 227 yards, including a 78-yard touchdown to Mark Ingram, and No. 11 Alabama rolled to a 30-10 win over No. 17 Mississippi State on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ingram, No. 12 Bama roll over No. 19 Miss. St.

events.name: Iowa Hawkeyes at Northwestern Wildcats

headlines.description: Dan Persa threw for 318 yards and two late touchdowns before being helped off the field, and Northwestern handed No. 13 Iowa another devastating loss, beating the Hawkeyes 21-17 on Saturday.

events.name: Utah Utes at Notre Dame Fighting Irish

headlines.description: Freshman Tommy Rees threw three touchdown passes in his first collegiate start and Notre Dame used two Utah special teams mistakes Saturday to rout the slumping Utes 28-3.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rees sparks Irish's upset win over Utah

events.name: UTEP Miners at Arkansas Razorbacks

headlines.description: Ryan Mallett threw for a school-record five touchdowns and ran for another as Arkansas defeated Texas-El Paso 58-21 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mallett breaks TD mark as No. 15 Arkansas rolls

events.name: Texas Tech Red Raiders at Oklahoma Sooners

headlines.description: Ryan Broyles caught three of Landry Jones' five touchdown passes and broke a few more Oklahoma records, leading the Sooners to a 45-7 victory against Texas Tech on Saturday.

events.name: Kansas State Wildcats at Missouri Tigers

headlines.description: Blaine Gabbert accounted for three touchdowns in a strong bounceback effort and Missouri made just as many big plays on defense in a 38-28 victory over error-prone Kansas State in its home finale Saturday.

events.name: USC Trojans at Arizona Wildcats

headlines.description: Marc Tyler ran for a career-high 160 yards and Southern California climbed into a tie with Arizona for third in the Pac-10 with a 24-21 victory over the 18th-ranked Wildcats on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: USC leads early, holds off fading No. 18 Arizona

events.name: Virginia Tech Hokies at North Carolina Tar Heels

headlines.description: Tyrod Taylor hit Marcus Davis with a pair of third-quarter touchdown passes to help Virginia Tech beat North Carolina 26-10 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Taylor TDs drive Virginia Tech by UNC

events.name: Nevada Wolf Pack at Fresno State Bulldogs

headlines.description: Colin Kaepernick set a school record with two more rushing touchdowns, and Vai Taua's third score of the night gave No. 21 Nevada a 35-34 win over Fresno State on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Taua's 3rd TD vaults Nevada past Fresno State

events.name: South Carolina Gamecocks at Florida Gators

headlines.description: The Ol' Ball Coach notched a huge win at his ol' stomping grounds.

events.name: Texas A&M Aggies at Baylor Bears

headlines.description: Cyrus Gray ran for 137 yards and scored three of his career-high four touchdowns in the second half as No. 23 Texas A&M rallied from a 16-point first-half deficit for a 42-30 win over Baylor on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gray's big 2nd half lifts Texas A&M over Baylor

events.name: Miami Hurricanes at Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets

headlines.description: ATLANTA -- Freshman Stephen Morris passed for 230 yards and a touchdown to win the matchup of backup quarterbacks and Miami beat Georgia Tech 35-10 on Saturday to stay alive in the ACC's Coastal Division.
headlines.shortLinkText: Miami handles Ga. Tech in battle of backups

events.name: South Florida Bulls at Louisville Cardinals

headlines.description: Sophomore kicker Maikon Bonani hit a 37-yard field goal in overtime to give South Florida a 24-21 win against Louisville Saturday as the Bulls become bowl eligible for the sixth straight season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bonani's FG lifts bowl-eligible USF in overtime

events.name: Boston College Eagles at Duke Blue Devils

headlines.description: Chase Rettig threw two third-quarter touchdown passes and Boston College made a late defensive stand to defeat Duke 21-16 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rettig tosses 2 TDs;  BC holds on to nip Duke

events.name: Cincinnati Bearcats at West Virginia Mountaineers

headlines.description: MORGANTOWN, W.Va. -- Geno Smith threw four first-half touchdown passes, West Virginia frustrated Big East passing leader Zach Collaros and the Mountaineers beat Cincinnati 37-10 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: West Virginia's first-half barrage douses Cincy

events.name: Minnesota Golden Gophers at Illinois Fighting Illini

headlines.description: DeLeon Eskridge rescued Minnesota from its tenth loss Saturday, leading the Gophers to a 38-34 comeback upset of Illinois with a last-minute touchdown run.
headlines.shortLinkText: Eskridge's 3rd TD caps Gophers' rally vs. Illinois

events.name: Southern Mississippi Golden Eagles at UCF Knights

headlines.description: Austin Davis threw for 264 yards and four touchdowns Saturday, helping Southern Mississippi rally to ruin Central Florida's first national ranking with a 31-21 victory that also keeps the Eagles in the race for Conference USA's East Division title.
headlines.shortLinkText: Davis' 4 TDs help Southern Miss rally past UCF

events.name: Michigan Wolverines at Purdue Boilermakers

headlines.description: Denard Robinson overcame four turnovers, and Michigan defeated Purdue 27-16 on Saturday.

events.name: Ole Miss Rebels at Tennessee Volunteers

headlines.description: Tyler Bray threw three touchdown passes, two of them to Justin Hunter, and Tauren Poole ran for two more as Tennessee got its first Southeastern Conference win of the season with a 52-14 victory over Mississippi on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tennessee tops Ole Miss for 1st SEC win of year

events.name: Vanderbilt Commodores at Kentucky Wildcats

headlines.description: Randall Cobb ran for a career-high 170 yards and two touchdowns as Kentucky surged past Vanderbilt 38-20 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kentucky bowl eligible after racing past Vandy

events.name: Delaware Blue Hens at UMass Minutemen

headlines.description: Delaware 45, Massachusetts 27

events.name: Liberty Flames at Coastal Carolina Chanticleers

headlines.description: Coastal Carolina 45, Liberty 31

events.name: Iowa State Cyclones at Colorado Buffaloes

headlines.description: Interim coach Brian Cabral won his debut for Colorado on Saturday when Cody Hawkins threw three touchdown passes and Rodney Stewart ran for 123 yards in the Buffaloes' 34-14 victory over Iowa State.
headlines.shortLinkText: Colorado coach Cabral wins debut vs. Iowa St.

headlines.description: James Madison 30, William &amp, Mary 24

events.name: BYU Cougars at Colorado State Rams

headlines.description: BYU 49, Colorado St. 10

events.name: Wake Forest Demon Deacons at NC State Wolfpack

headlines.description: Russell Wilson threw for two touchdowns and ran for two more in what might have been his final home game to lead North Carolina State past Wake Forest 38-3 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wilson shines as NC State stomps Wake Forest

events.name: Syracuse Orange at Rutgers Scarlet Knights

headlines.description: Freshman Ross Krautman kicked a 24-yard field goal with 1:07 to play and Syracuse defeated Rutgers 13-10 to become bowl eligible for the first time since 2004.

events.name: Maryland Terrapins at Virginia Cavaliers

headlines.description: D.J. Adams ran for three touchdowns and Danny O'Brien ran for one and threw for two, leading Maryland to a 42-23 victory against Virginia on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Adams, O'Brien help Maryland run over Virginia

events.name: VMI Keydets at Old Dominion Monarchs
North Texas Mean Green at Middle Tennessee Blue Raiders

headlines.description: Lance Dunbar rushed for 226 yards and a touchdown as North Texas snapped a four-game losing streak against Middle Tennessee in a 23-17 win Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: North Texas ends drought vs. Middle Tennessee

headlines.description: Tulane 54, Rice 49

events.name: Washington State Cougars at Oregon State Beavers

headlines.description: Quarterback Jeff Tuel passed for 157 yards and rushed for 79 Saturday as Washington State snapped a 16-game conference losing streak with a 31-14 win over Oregon State.

headlines.description: Louisiana Tech 41, New Mexico St. 20

events.name: Clemson Tigers at Florida State Seminoles

headlines.description: A week after missing a game-winning kick in the final seconds, Dustin Hopkins booted a career-best 55-yard field goal Saturday night as time expired to give Florida State a 16-13 victory over Clemson.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hopkins, Florida St. boot Clemson; Ponder sits
